Often we get users asking about searches not working as expected in confluence.  Pointing them to the online doco (http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF20/Searching+Confluence or http://lucene.apache.org/java/docs/queryparsersyntax.html for more advanced stuff) normally solves the problem.

It would be good if there was a link on the search screen direct to the documentation, or a popup similar to the wiki notation help popup with advice on searching and the syntax to use.

(I notice in Jira, there are question marks in a few places that link to the online documentation, something similar in confluence would be handy.)

