I'm trying to use the Confluence blog functionality to produce a typical looking blog site. I'm getting very close, but one thing that I haven't been able to work out is how to show a concise 'Previous Posts' section. For example, I'd like to base my section on this site (on the right, one page down):

  http://xooglers.blogspot.com/

I'd hoped that this would do what I wanted:

  {blog-posts:5|content=titles} 

but that renders the titles within a table with multiple columns (Title, Author, Date Posted).

I'd really like to have a stripped down option that just renders the articles in a <ul> with a unique class so that I can style it in CSS. Based on how other macros work, maybe this should be a 'style=ul' option.

I know that the plugins are all open source now so I could go implement this myself, but I'm hoping that this seems useful enough that you'll do it for me. :-) If not, any hints you can give me as to how to write this myself would be gratefully appreciated.

