Plugin manager events (like Install, Uninstall, Startup, Shutdown, Enable, Disable) should poke the respective plugins so that they can perform assossiated logic, such as shutting down any open JDBC link, or connecting to a server to say "I'm alive" - or any reason a plugin developer chooses.

There are a number of ways this could be done - and the one I like most (at the time of writing) is the modules themselves could implement PluginInstalled, PluginEnabled (etc) interfaces, and the class is instanciated and the method in the interface called during the event. If  there is already an instance (such as in the case of a component) it should be used, otherwise in the case of a macro it could be created and destroyed just for the event calling.

Other implementation ideas welcome! (Feel free to pick holes in my idea too)

